  "prompt": "Are there legal obligations for financial institutions regarding money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, financial institutions have significant legal obligations regarding anti-money laundering (AML) efforts, including:\n\n1. Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Verify customer identities\n- Conduct background checks\n- Monitor suspicious transactions\n\n2. Reporting requirements\n- File Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Report cash transactions over certain thresholds\n- Notify authorities about potential illegal activities\n\n3. Compliance regulations\n- Follow Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) guidelines\n- Implement internal AML control procedures\n- Maintain transaction records\n\n4. Risk assessment\n- Develop risk management strategies\n- Screen customers against watchlists\n- Conduct ongoing due diligence\n\n5. Training obligations\n- Educate employees about money laundering risks\n- Provide regular compliance training\n- Maintain current knowledge of regulations\n\n6. Potential penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential criminal liability\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\nThese obligations are designed to prevent financial crimes and help law enforcement track potentially illegal financial activities.",
